I [[Captain (British Army and Royal Marines)|Captain]] '''Sir Richard Francis Burton''' [[Order of St Michael and St George|KCMG]] [[Royal Geographic Society|FRGS]] (19 Marzo 1821 &ndash; 20 Octubre 1890) metung yang Ingles a [[heograpu]] (''geographer''), talapaglakbe, [[talapaglikas]] (''translator''), [[talasulat]], [[sundalus]], [[oriental studies|orientalista]], [[cartographer]] (''cartographer''), [[ethnologist]] (''ethnologist''), [[ispiya]], [[linguistics|linguista]], [[poetry|poeta]], [[fencing|talapag-espada]] ampong [[diplomatiku]]. Pikabaluan ya kareng kayang pamaglakbe king Asia, Africa ampo reng Americas, ampo ing kayang e karaniwan a beluan kareng amanu ampong kultura. agpang king metung a pamamilang, byasa yang magsalitang 29 (adwang pulu't syam) a amanung Europeu, Asianu ampong Aprikanu.<ref>Lovell (1998), p. xvii.</ref>

==Notes==
:1.{{note|a}} Burton later expressed his own doubts about the death by writing "The calamity had been the more unexpected as he was ever remarkable for the caution with which he handled his weapons."<ref>Godsall, p. 255</ref>

